9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 543, L.D. 857, “An Act to Increase
10 Government Transparency in the Procurement of Goods and Services”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §1825-B, sub-§15 is enacted to read:
14 15. Records. Beginning January 1, 2026, the Director of the Bureau of General
15 Services shall preserve, consistent with applicable record retention schedules established
16 and published by the Department of the Secretary of State, Maine State Archives, and make
17 available on a publicly accessible website all records and documents regarding the
18 competitive bidding process, including notices of intent to waive competitive bidding under
19 this section and supporting documents and competitive solicitations and supporting
20 documents, including question-and-answer summaries, evaluation team packets and award
21 decision letters. All proposals submitted in response to a solicitation and resulting in an
22 award are public documents, unless otherwise excepted by statute.
23 Sec. 2. Record recovery. The Department of Administrative and Financial Services
24 shall to the extent possible recover and publish on a publicly accessible website all past
25 notices of intent to waive the competitive bidding process and supporting documents.'
26 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
27 number to read consecutively.
28 SUMMARY
2299 This amendment amends the bill by establishing a start date of January 1, 2026 for the
3300 statutory requirements of the bill. The amendment changes these requirements to specify
3311 that the Director of the Bureau of General Services must preserve, consistent with
3322 applicable record retention schedules established and published by the Department of the
3333 Secretary of State, Maine State Archives, and make available on a publicly accessible
3344 website all records and documents regarding the competitive bidding process, including
3355 notices of intent to waive competitive bidding and supporting documents and competitive
